==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prolocutor
<hw>Prol`o*cu"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from
<ets>proloqui</ets>, p. p. <ets>prolocutus</ets>, to speak out;
<ets>pro</ets> for + <ets>loqui</ets> to speak.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who speaks for another.</def>
<rj><au>Jeffrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The presiding officer of a convocation.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolocutorship</ent>⟦br⟧
